<doc id="78365" wikidata="Q392401" url="?curid=78365" title="Agelasta">
<text>In Greek mythology, Agelasta (, , &quot;smile-less&quot;) was the name of the stone on which Demeter rested during her search for Persephone.

In modern culture, Agelasta inspired the title of a documentary by Philippos Koutsaftis (Φίλιππος Κουτσαφτής), called &quot;Agelastos Petra&quot; (&quot;Αγέλαστος Πέτρα&quot;, &quot;smile-less stone&quot;, 2000).

